headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 33 points and handed out 15 assists, Myles Turner added 21 points and the Indiana Pacers rolled past the Miami Heat 128-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 33 and hands out 15 assists, leading Pacers to 128-115 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 33 points, nine assists and eight rebounds, and the Boston Celtics beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 118-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum's big night lifts short-handed Celtics past Timberwolves 118-115

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored 26 points, Cam Thomas had 24 and the Brooklyn Nets withstood a frantic Milwaukee comeback attempt down the stretch to beat the Bucks 113-110 on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets build big lead and barely hang on down the stretch for 113-110 victory over Bucks

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 29 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder won their franchise-record 13th consecutive regular-season game, 116-98 over the Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 29 points and Thunder win 13th in a row, 116-98 over Clippers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 30 points and made all eight of his 3-point attempts, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Philadelphia 76ers 139-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 30 points, makes all 8 3-point attempts in Warriors' 139-105 win over 76ers

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 38 points, Max Christie had a career-high 28 and the Los Angeles Lakers overcame Anthony Davis' absence for a 114-106 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James, Max Christie carry Lakers past Blazers 114-106 for their 6th win in 8 games
